Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice into a #medium saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}. Stir in the @Basmati Rice{150%g} and @salt{1/4%tsp} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid. Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, heat a drizzle of oil in a #large frying pan{} on medium-high heat. Once hot, add the @Diced British Chicken Breast{1%pack} and season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. Fry until browned all over, ~{5-6%minutes}. Turn occasionally. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw chicken and its packaging.

While the chicken fries, peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{2}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}). Halve the @Baby Plum Tomatoes{125%g} and pop them into a #bowl{}. Halve the @Lime{1}. Roughly chop the @Coriander{1%bunch} (stalks and all). Add half the coriander to the bowl of tomatoes. Drizzle in some @olive oil{drizzle}, squeeze in some lime juice, then season with salt and pepper. Mix well, then set your pico de gallo aside.

Once the chicken has browned, add the garlic and stir-fry for ~{1%minute}. Stir in the @Tomato Passata{1%carton}, @Chicken Stock Paste{10%g}, @Chipotle Paste{20%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder), @Sugar{1%tsp} for the sauce and @Water{125%ml} for the sauce. Bring to the boil, then lower the heat and simmer gently until the sauce has thickened and the chicken is cooked through, ~{8-10%minutes}. IMPORTANT: The chicken is cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

Meanwhile, halve the @Avocado{1} and remove the stone. Use a #tablespoon{} to scoop the flesh out into a bowl. Add a squeeze of lime juice and season with salt and pepper, then mash with a #fork{}. Taste and add more salt, pepper and lime juice if needed, then set your guacamole aside.

Grate the @Mature Cheddar Cheese{40%g}.

When the chicken is ready, taste and season with salt and pepper if needed, then remove from the heat. Stir through the @Butter{10%g} until melted and glossy.

Spoon the rice into your #serving bowls{} and top with the chipotle chicken, then sprinkle over the cheese. Finish with a dollop of guacamole, pico de gallo, @Soured Cream{75%g} and a sprinkle of the remaining coriander. Serve with any remaining lime cut into wedges for squeezing over. Enjoy!